      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Expecting the Great Square form to come to the fore so it is hard to go away from the winner of that race, JILLIBY DREAMLOVER (2). She did a great job there, coming from a wider draw and leading early before surrendering but using the sprint lane to score by 5m. She has Group 1 form around the likes of Keayang Zahara and Jilliby Ballerini this season. The good draw can her strike again. Kiwi visitor DASH DOSH NZ (3) continued her good form from across the Tasman when chasing JILLIBY DREAMLOVER as runner-up in her Australian debut. Should enjoy a nice run from this draw so could turn the tables I AM HELLBOUND (5) drew on the back row and did plenty of work in the Great Square so was brave in finishing fourth. Had won five of his previous six starts so is tough to knock. CRACKERJACK NZ (7) followed up a debut Australian win with an eye-catching third from the back line in the Great Square. Draws wide but clearly has talent.",
